        <para>After you have chosen one of the input templates, you need to supply information about which language and script the publication utilises, and which
            transliteration scheme you utilise if you choose to transliterate the bibliographical information. Choose here which transliteration scheme from the list you
            follow. If any valid schemes are missing, please open a <ulink href="http://kjc-sv007.kjc.uni-heidelberg.de/helpdesk/open.php">ticket</ulink>.</para>
        
        <para>Decide which language you intend to use for cataloguing. This mainly applies to the description of the contents of the publication.
            For example, do you supply keywords in English, German or Chinese? As the
            official language of the Cluster is English, English is suggested (and the script therefore Latin), but you have the option to choose other languages.</para>
